module.exports = {"data":{"post":{"id":"/Users/munniche/Documents/js-web-hack/1/shootmenow/content/posts/2019-04-19--how-did-i-build-this-blog/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","html":"<p>So this is not a comprehensive howto - just don’t have time to provide that (google is your friend).  However there are some pointers I can provide when working with Gatsby.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Install prereq’s (npm,gatsby)</li>\n<li>Choose a well supported template that suits your use case.  I looked for a template that supported SEO, tags, simple interface, fast and simple to navigate for viewer.  I also wanted some module support to mark the Mark Down pretty.</li>\n<li>The content is saved to the /public folder which can be uploaded to S3 / your favourite hosting service.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Learnings from today</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\">\n      <pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">When Training:\n\nWhen presenting training, above all, show confidence &amp; enthusiasm \nas this will help you help the audience to retain the content presented. </code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h4>Links</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>NPM - <a href=\"https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm\">https://docs.npmjs.com/downloading-and-installing-node-js-and-npm</a></li>\n<li>Gatsby - <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/quick-start/\">https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/quick-start/</a></li>\n<li>Hosting a Page on Github - <a href=\"https://pages.github.com\">https://pages.github.com</a></li>\n</ul>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So this is not a comprehensive howto - just don’t have time to provide that (google is your friend).  However there are some pointers I can provide when working with Gatsby."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ol","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li